1
00:00:11,875 --> 00:00:12,750
[YOU]
Previously on,

2
00:00:12,833 --> 00:00:14,166
[GIRLS]
<i>Love Live! Sunshine!!</i>

3
00:00:14,250 --> 00:00:15,708
[YOU]
With Mu's as her guiding light,

4
00:00:15,791 --> 00:00:18,375
Chika was inspired to start a
School Idol Club of her own!

5
00:00:18,458 --> 00:00:20,125
Things didn't really
go as planned.

6
00:00:20,208 --> 00:00:21,166
[DIA]
I refuse your application.

7
00:00:21,250 --> 00:00:22,375
[YOU]
After that,

8
00:00:22,458 --> 00:00:24,458
Chika met a piano player
visiting from Tokyo,

9
00:00:24,541 --> 00:00:26,958
and shared her big dream
of becoming a School Idol!

10
00:00:27,041 --> 00:00:28,291
[RIKO]
Let go of me! Get off!

11
00:00:28,375 --> 00:00:30,625
[CHIKA] I wanted to do
this with my own friends.

12
00:00:30,708 --> 00:00:33,125
[YOU] In order have a school
idol group, Chika has to find

13
00:00:33,208 --> 00:00:35,333
a student who can compose
music for the group.

14
00:00:35,416 --> 00:00:36,916
And wouldn't ya know it?

15
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:39,708
Riko, the girl she met by the
sea, transferred to our school!

16
00:00:39,791 --> 00:00:41,625
[CHIKA]
It's a miracle!

17
00:00:41,708 --> 00:00:44,416
[ANNOUNCER 2A] Presenting
Otonokizaka High first year,

18
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:46,208
Riko Sakurauchi.

19
00:00:46,291 --> 00:00:49,333
Performing, "Those Who
Return to the Sea."

20
00:00:49,416 --> 00:00:52,708
[applause]

21
00:00:55,958 --> 00:00:59,500
[gasping]

22
00:00:59,583 --> 00:01:03,458
[AUDIENCE murmuring]

23
00:01:05,541 --> 00:01:08,583
[RIKO cries]

24
00:02:50,041 --> 00:02:51,000
I'm sorry.

25
00:02:51,083 --> 00:02:52,166
If you'd just hear me out,

26
00:02:52,250 --> 00:02:55,625
I think you'd be a great
fit for our club!

27
00:02:55,708 --> 00:02:57,458
[groans]

28
00:02:57,541 --> 00:02:58,958
[RIKO]
I'm sorry.

29
00:02:59,041 --> 00:03:01,250
When Otonokizaka High
was about to shut down,

30
00:03:01,333 --> 00:03:02,833
the school idols saved it!

31
00:03:02,916 --> 00:03:03,958
[STUDENTS gasp]

32
00:03:07,666 --> 00:03:08,916
[CHIKA whines]

33
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,166
[YOU laughs]

34
00:03:10,250 --> 00:03:11,791
[CHIKA panting]
What we're really looking for

35
00:03:11,875 --> 00:03:13,583
is someone who can
compose music, ya know?

36
00:03:13,666 --> 00:03:15,333
[RIKO]
I'm sorry!

37
00:03:15,416 --> 00:03:17,291
[CHIKA]
Wait! Ah!

38
00:03:17,375 --> 00:03:18,708
Jeez. That's sad.

39
00:03:18,791 --> 00:03:20,125
[laughs sheepishly]

40
00:03:20,208 --> 00:03:21,916
[CHIKA]
One, two! One, two!

41
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,875
One, two! One, two!

42
00:03:23,958 --> 00:03:24,791
One, two...

43
00:03:24,875 --> 00:03:26,000
[YOU]
Did you break her yet?

44
00:03:26,083 --> 00:03:26,791
[CHIKA]
Nope!

45
00:03:26,875 --> 00:03:28,041
But although she said no,

46
00:03:28,125 --> 00:03:30,833
I know that she knows
she wants to say yes.

47
00:03:30,916 --> 00:03:32,708
[YOU]
Oh, yeah?

48
00:03:35,458 --> 00:03:37,250
[YOU sighs]

49
00:03:37,333 --> 00:03:38,833
In the beginning,
she was like...

50
00:03:38,916 --> 00:03:40,166
[RIKO]
I'm sorry!

51
00:03:40,250 --> 00:03:42,375
But now it's unsure,
kind of like a...

52
00:03:42,458 --> 00:03:44,708
[RIKO]
Uh. I... I'm sorry.

53
00:03:44,791 --> 00:03:46,333
It's only a matter of time!

54
00:03:46,416 --> 00:03:48,708
Hate to break it to ya,
but she might just be annoyed.

55
00:03:48,791 --> 00:03:49,958
I'm not too worried.

56
00:03:50,041 --> 00:03:52,333
If worse comes to worse,
leave it to me!

57
00:03:52,416 --> 00:03:53,875
I've got this!

58
00:03:53,958 --> 00:03:55,458
Well... You can teach yourself,

59
00:03:55,541 --> 00:03:57,625
but I'd like to do this
before we're old ladies.

60
00:03:57,708 --> 00:03:59,750
So how's everything
going on your end?

61
00:03:59,833 --> 00:04:02,666
[YOU]
Ah-ha! I'll show you!

62
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:03,916
I don't know...

63
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:04,750
Well...?

64
00:04:04,833 --> 00:04:06,291
[CHIKA]
It's pretty neat.

65
00:04:06,375 --> 00:04:09,791
But it looks more like a uniform
than a school idol costume.

66
00:04:09,875 --> 00:04:11,833
Do you have any
designs with skirts?

67
00:04:11,916 --> 00:04:13,791
[YOU]
Sure do! Here!

68
00:04:13,875 --> 00:04:16,875
[CHIKA] Ah, well, okay, but it
doesn't look like a costume.

69
00:04:16,958 --> 00:04:19,333
What about something super
cute and unique, you know?

70
00:04:19,416 --> 00:04:20,916
[YOU]
Oh, then you'll love this!

71
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:21,791
Here!

72
00:04:21,875 --> 00:04:23,250
[CHIKA]
Why do I have a gun?

73
00:04:23,333 --> 00:04:24,833
[YOU]
It's adorable!

74
00:04:24,916 --> 00:04:27,791
Uh, but it might be hard
to dance in combat boots.

75
00:04:27,875 --> 00:04:28,708
[YOU]
Hm?

76
00:04:28,791 --> 00:04:30,375
[CHIKA]
Uh... We want to shine

77
00:04:30,458 --> 00:04:33,041
when people watch us perform,
so how about something bright?

78
00:04:33,125 --> 00:04:35,416
[YOU] I thought you'd say that,
so I came up with this design.

79
00:04:35,500 --> 00:04:36,666
Here!

80
00:04:36,750 --> 00:04:39,666
[CHIKA gasps]
Oh my gosh, it's just perfect!

81
00:04:39,750 --> 00:04:40,708
[YOU]
You like it?

82
00:04:40,791 --> 00:04:42,541
[CHIKA]
Can you really make this?

83
00:04:42,625 --> 00:04:45,000
[YOU] Mm-hm. It'll be
super easy to sew!

84
00:04:45,083 --> 00:04:46,875
Really? You're the best!

85
00:04:46,958 --> 00:04:49,250
Now there's nothing that
can stand in our way!

86
00:04:49,333 --> 00:04:51,166
Once again I refuse
your application!

87
00:04:51,250 --> 00:04:52,125
Are you for real?!

88
00:04:52,208 --> 00:04:53,708
We spoke too soon.

89
00:04:53,791 --> 00:04:56,250
[DIA] I've already said that you
need five people to form a club.

90
00:04:56,333 --> 00:04:57,333
And enlighten me,

91
00:04:57,416 --> 00:04:59,416
have you found a composer yet?

92
00:04:59,500 --> 00:05:00,625
Well the thing is,

93
00:05:00,708 --> 00:05:03,916
maybe, if we believe
with our hearts,

94
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:07,583
the perfect person will
sign up for sure!

95
00:05:07,666 --> 00:05:10,708
I'm not worried. I bet Mousse
didn't have it easy either

96
00:05:10,791 --> 00:05:13,750
when they were first
starting out. We got this.

97
00:05:13,833 --> 00:05:15,125
Have you ever heard of them?

98
00:05:15,208 --> 00:05:17,625
They were the underdog group
from Otonokizaka High

99
00:05:17,708 --> 00:05:19,208
who won the second Love Live!

100
00:05:19,291 --> 00:05:21,375
You know, Mousse!

101
00:05:23,375 --> 00:05:24,875
You must be confused.

102
00:05:24,958 --> 00:05:26,208
For a moment there,

103
00:05:26,291 --> 00:05:29,791
I thought you were actually
talking about Mu's.

104
00:05:29,875 --> 00:05:31,666
[CHIKA, YOU]
Hm...? Uh!

105
00:05:31,750 --> 00:05:33,333
[CHIKA]
Ah! Silly me!

106
00:05:33,416 --> 00:05:36,000
I didn't know it was
pronounced "Muse."

107
00:05:36,083 --> 00:05:38,125
[DIA]
Be quiet, you!

108
00:05:39,458 --> 00:05:40,833
So rude!

109
00:05:40,916 --> 00:05:44,250
She acted like I didn't know
what I was talking about.

110
00:05:44,333 --> 00:05:45,875
So... you give up?

111
00:05:45,958 --> 00:05:47,833
Not a chance!

112
00:05:47,916 --> 00:05:49,208
We got this!

113
00:05:49,291 --> 00:05:50,458
[CHIKA yelps]

114
00:05:50,541 --> 00:05:51,916
You have the audacity to
use them in your pitch,

115
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:53,791
and you don't even know how
to pronounce their name?!

116
00:05:53,875 --> 00:05:55,166
[YOU]
Huh?

117
00:05:55,250 --> 00:05:57,125
In the world of school idols,
Mu's are like gods!

118
00:05:57,208 --> 00:05:59,166
Such a mistake is sacrilege!

119
00:05:59,250 --> 00:06:00,708
They're record-breaking
geniuses,

120
00:06:00,791 --> 00:06:02,166
masters of their craft!

121
00:06:02,250 --> 00:06:03,083
They're everything!

122
00:06:03,166 --> 00:06:04,458
True legends.

123
00:06:04,541 --> 00:06:07,708
Thinking you could be
like them is ridiculous.

124
00:06:07,791 --> 00:06:10,958
Um. Isn't this a little close?

125
00:06:11,041 --> 00:06:12,916
[CHIKA]
Oh! It's Hanamaru!

126
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:14,375
Hi-ya!

127
00:06:14,458 --> 00:06:17,500
Hi! Good to see y'all!

128
00:06:17,583 --> 00:06:20,166
Oh my gosh, don't you think
she's super adorable?

129
00:06:20,250 --> 00:06:22,583
[gasps, growls]

130
00:06:22,666 --> 00:06:24,291
[HANAMARU]
Huh?

131
00:06:24,375 --> 00:06:25,458
[RUBY gasps]

132
00:06:25,541 --> 00:06:27,291
I see you hiding back
there, Ruby! Hey!

133
00:06:27,375 --> 00:06:30,125
[DIA] Hmph. Let me guess
how all this started.

134
00:06:30,208 --> 00:06:31,666
You stumbled upon
Mu's somewhere,

135
00:06:31,750 --> 00:06:33,458
and with your limited
knowledge you assumed

136
00:06:33,541 --> 00:06:35,583
that you might be able
to imitate them.

137
00:06:35,666 --> 00:06:36,791
No, that's not true.

138
00:06:36,875 --> 00:06:39,083
Tell me. What was the first song

139
00:06:39,166 --> 00:06:40,916
Mu's sang together
as a group of nine?

140
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,625
Any clue at all?

141
00:06:42,708 --> 00:06:43,625
I don't really...

142
00:06:43,708 --> 00:06:47,041
[DIA growls]
Eh! Time's up!

143
00:06:47,125 --> 00:06:50,000
C'mon, a little
closer. Just a bit.

144
00:06:50,083 --> 00:06:52,958
You know want it. [laughs]

145
00:06:53,041 --> 00:06:54,500
[gasps]

146
00:06:56,583 --> 00:06:57,875
[CHIKA]
Whoops!

147
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,500
[CHIKA]
So close!

148
00:07:00,583 --> 00:07:04,916
Aw. We're all friends here so
there's no need to be afraid!

149
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:06,000
All right!

150
00:07:06,083 --> 00:07:07,083
[RUBY screams]

151
00:07:07,166 --> 00:07:11,208
[CHIKA laughs]
Got ya! Give us a hug!

152
00:07:11,291 --> 00:07:13,375
[DIA]
"Bokurano Live, Keemitono Life."

153
00:07:13,458 --> 00:07:15,166
AKA "Borarara."

154
00:07:15,250 --> 00:07:18,041
Next up. Do you happen to
have any idea which venue

155
00:07:18,125 --> 00:07:21,958
Mu's and A-RISE chose for
the second Love Live prelims?

156
00:07:22,041 --> 00:07:24,291
The venue? Um.

157
00:07:24,375 --> 00:07:25,875
[DIA]
Eh! Eh! Time's up!

158
00:07:25,958 --> 00:07:26,958
[CHIKA gasps]

159
00:07:27,041 --> 00:07:29,500
The rooftop of Akihabara's
UTX High.

160
00:07:29,583 --> 00:07:32,708
It's so simple to best you
that it's actually pathetic.

161
00:07:32,791 --> 00:07:35,041
Moving on. Tell me
what Mu's sang

162
00:07:35,125 --> 00:07:37,291
for their encore at the
second Love Live finals.

163
00:07:37,375 --> 00:07:40,916
I know that!
"Bokurawaimano Nka de"!

164
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,583
I wasn't finished.

165
00:07:43,291 --> 00:07:45,291
How long have we had
a School Idol Club?

166
00:07:45,375 --> 00:07:46,833
Well, we're starting
it this year!

167
00:07:46,916 --> 00:07:48,166
You wanna join us?

168
00:07:48,250 --> 00:07:50,375
[HANAMARU] Uh. I signed
up to be a library helper,

169
00:07:50,458 --> 00:07:51,958
but it sounds fun, zura.

170
00:07:52,041 --> 00:07:53,875
I mean... it sounds fun.

171
00:07:53,958 --> 00:07:55,833
[CHIKA] I gotcha.
What about you, Ruby?

172
00:07:55,916 --> 00:07:58,416
[gasps] Well... I, uh...

173
00:07:58,500 --> 00:08:01,666
I'm not too sure about it.
Gotta think about my sister.

174
00:08:01,750 --> 00:08:03,041
Who's your sister?

175
00:08:03,125 --> 00:08:04,166
Dia is.

176
00:08:04,250 --> 00:08:05,916
It makes things a
little complicated.

177
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:08,291
Ah! You gotta be kidding me.

178
00:08:08,375 --> 00:08:10,541
Yeah, she's against having
a School Idol Club.

179
00:08:10,625 --> 00:08:12,208
We tried everything.

180
00:08:12,291 --> 00:08:13,708
I know.

181
00:08:13,791 --> 00:08:16,375
[DIA] Continuing. What are the
names of the four members

182
00:08:16,458 --> 00:08:18,500
skipping in the opening
choreography?

183
00:08:18,583 --> 00:08:20,041
[CHIKA whines]

184
00:08:20,125 --> 00:08:22,041
[DIA]
Boop, boop, boop!

185
00:08:22,125 --> 00:08:24,333
--Err! Time's up!
--[PA system screeching]

186
00:08:24,416 --> 00:08:27,166
[STUDENTS gasping]

187
00:08:27,958 --> 00:08:30,333
[DIA]
Eli Ayase, Nozomi Tojo,

188
00:08:30,416 --> 00:08:33,125
Rin Hoshizora,
and Maki Nishikino.

189
00:08:33,208 --> 00:08:34,791
The fact you don't know
that is embarrassing.

190
00:08:34,875 --> 00:08:36,791
[CHIKA]
I... I guess it is.

191
00:08:36,875 --> 00:08:39,291
Wow, so you're like a huge
Mu's fan, aren't you?

192
00:08:39,375 --> 00:08:40,708
[DIA]
That should go without saying.

193
00:08:40,791 --> 00:08:42,291
Obviously I know what I'm--

194
00:08:42,375 --> 00:08:44,750
Uh! Uh... Th-This
kind of information

195
00:08:44,833 --> 00:08:46,250
is general knowledge!

196
00:08:46,333 --> 00:08:47,791
[BOTH chuckle]

197
00:08:47,875 --> 00:08:49,333
Well, regardless!

198
00:08:49,416 --> 00:08:52,916
I will never approve
a School Idol Club!

199
00:08:57,708 --> 00:08:59,208
[YOU]
Okay.

200
00:08:59,291 --> 00:09:01,791
We should change tactics and get
more of our materials together.

201
00:09:01,875 --> 00:09:04,000
She'd have to take us seriously!

202
00:09:04,083 --> 00:09:05,375
I'll try anything.

203
00:09:05,458 --> 00:09:07,750
Wait a second, didn't
we just miss your stop?

204
00:09:07,833 --> 00:09:10,875
No. I have to drop off a
notebook in Numazu today.

205
00:09:10,958 --> 00:09:11,833
What for?

206
00:09:11,916 --> 00:09:12,958
[HANAMARU]
Well,

207
00:09:13,041 --> 00:09:15,291
it started on the
first day of school.

208
00:09:15,375 --> 00:09:17,750
To those of you clinging
to your weak mortal coils,

209
00:09:17,833 --> 00:09:20,416
Yohane offers the
deal of a lifetime.

210
00:09:20,500 --> 00:09:23,208
As my demons... Heh, heh.

211
00:09:26,041 --> 00:09:27,875
Crap!

212
00:09:29,083 --> 00:09:30,250
[HANAMARU]
It was weird.

213
00:09:30,333 --> 00:09:32,375
And I haven't seen her
at school since then!

214
00:09:32,458 --> 00:09:34,416
Looks like you're stuck!

215
00:09:35,833 --> 00:09:39,625
[CHIKA panting]
See you!

216
00:09:42,541 --> 00:09:44,708
How are you doing, Riko?

217
00:09:44,791 --> 00:09:45,583
[gasps]

218
00:09:45,666 --> 00:09:46,791
[exhales]

219
00:09:46,875 --> 00:09:47,750
[footsteps]

220
00:09:47,833 --> 00:09:49,000
[CHIKA]
Let's see here.

221
00:09:49,083 --> 00:09:51,916
You're not gonna try to
jump in again, are you?

222
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:53,375
No, I'm not!

223
00:09:53,458 --> 00:09:54,750
That's a relief.

224
00:09:54,833 --> 00:09:57,041
Well then... You need
to know that even though

225
00:09:57,125 --> 00:09:59,333
you followed me here,
my answer won't change.

226
00:09:59,416 --> 00:10:03,625
Huh? Oh, I know that!
I was just saying hiya!

227
00:10:03,708 --> 00:10:08,208
So anyway, the ocean. Have
you figured the sound out yet?

228
00:10:11,291 --> 00:10:14,000
[CHIKA] In that case,
are you free on Sunday?

229
00:10:14,083 --> 00:10:15,291
Think so.

230
00:10:15,375 --> 00:10:17,125
[CHIKA]
If you come here around noon,

231
00:10:17,208 --> 00:10:18,541
you might hear it.

232
00:10:18,625 --> 00:10:20,250
The special sound
you're looking for.

233
00:10:20,333 --> 00:10:23,208
And if that happens you'll force
me to become a school idol?

234
00:10:23,291 --> 00:10:26,083
[CHIKA]
Ah. I totally would if I could.

235
00:10:26,166 --> 00:10:28,208
But it'd be better if
you wanted to join.

236
00:10:28,291 --> 00:10:29,291
Ya know?

237
00:10:29,375 --> 00:10:30,666
[RIKO]
Really?

238
00:10:30,750 --> 00:10:32,125
Look, you don't know anything
about school idols,

239
00:10:32,208 --> 00:10:33,958
but I'd love the
chance to show you.

240
00:10:34,041 --> 00:10:36,083
And who knows?
Maybe you'd like it!

241
00:10:36,166 --> 00:10:38,250
Is that okay?

242
00:10:38,333 --> 00:10:41,833
[sighs] Remember back
when we first met,

243
00:10:41,916 --> 00:10:43,416
I told you that I play piano?

244
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:44,875
[CHIKA]
Mm-hm.

245
00:10:44,958 --> 00:10:47,583
[RIKO] I've loved music
since I was a little girl.

246
00:10:47,666 --> 00:10:51,125
But lately, despite my attempts,
I'm not improving.

247
00:10:51,208 --> 00:10:53,583
I haven't even had
the motivation to play.

248
00:10:53,666 --> 00:10:56,458
I thought a change of
scenery would inspire me.

249
00:10:56,541 --> 00:10:58,541
If I could hear the ocean,

250
00:10:58,625 --> 00:11:02,000
I thought maybe
something would change.

251
00:11:04,125 --> 00:11:07,583
[CHIKA]
Something is going to change.

252
00:11:08,916 --> 00:11:11,000
How can you be so sure?

253
00:11:11,083 --> 00:11:15,833
No idea! I can just
feel it in my heart.

254
00:11:15,916 --> 00:11:19,041
You're really strange, but nice.

255
00:11:19,125 --> 00:11:20,500
Thanks, Chika.

256
00:11:20,583 --> 00:11:22,916
But I don't really have the
time to be a school idol.

257
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:24,916
I'm sorry.

258
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:25,875
Uh?

259
00:11:25,958 --> 00:11:27,458
It's okay!

260
00:11:27,541 --> 00:11:29,916
But, I still wanna help you find
the sound you're looking for.

261
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:32,208
I have a few ideas
that might help you out.

262
00:11:32,291 --> 00:11:33,041
[RIKO]
Huh?

263
00:11:33,125 --> 00:11:35,208
Would you be okay with that?

264
00:11:41,625 --> 00:11:44,833
I've never met
someone like you.

265
00:11:45,291 --> 00:11:48,166
[GIRLS]
Love Live! Sunshine!!

266
00:11:48,250 --> 00:11:50,833
[KANAN] So, you transferred
from Otonokizaka High?

267
00:11:50,916 --> 00:11:53,708
[CHIKA] Can you believe it?
The school Mu's is from!

268
00:11:53,791 --> 00:11:54,916
[RIKO]
Is that a big deal?

269
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:57,291
[KANAN]
Well, to a lot of people!

270
00:12:01,291 --> 00:12:02,458
[RIKO]
Imagine...

271
00:12:02,541 --> 00:12:04,208
[KANAN] Human ears can't
hear well underwater,

272
00:12:04,291 --> 00:12:06,875
but I think diving will give
you another perspective.

273
00:12:06,958 --> 00:12:09,750
Pretend that your body is
an actual part of the ocean.

274
00:12:09,833 --> 00:12:11,041
It's so peaceful down there,

275
00:12:11,125 --> 00:12:12,916
it'll be like a completely
different world.

276
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:15,875
So, you're telling me
just to use my imagination?

277
00:12:15,958 --> 00:12:18,083
Yup, that's exactly
what I'm saying.

278
00:12:18,166 --> 00:12:19,500
Can you do it?

279
00:12:19,583 --> 00:12:21,625
[RIKO]
I'll try.

280
00:12:29,916 --> 00:12:31,458
[gasping]

281
00:12:31,541 --> 00:12:33,000
[YOU]
Anything?

282
00:12:33,083 --> 00:12:34,833
I haven't heard it yet.

283
00:12:34,916 --> 00:12:38,333
It might take some time.
You're diving for inspiration.

284
00:12:38,416 --> 00:12:41,666
[RIKO] True. I didn't expect
it to be so dark down there.

285
00:12:41,750 --> 00:12:42,666
Tough to see?

286
00:12:42,750 --> 00:12:43,750
Let's go!

287
00:12:43,833 --> 00:12:47,375
We can all dive together
one more time.

288
00:12:47,458 --> 00:12:49,958
[splashing]

289
00:13:30,125 --> 00:13:35,083
[piano plays]

290
00:13:51,875 --> 00:13:53,708
Did you hear it?

291
00:13:53,791 --> 00:13:54,916
Yes.

292
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,750
Call me crazy, but I
think I heard it too.

293
00:13:56,833 --> 00:13:59,916
[YOU]
So did I! It was beautiful!

294
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:04,833
[ALL laughing]

295
00:14:07,750 --> 00:14:10,041
[bell tolls]

296
00:14:10,125 --> 00:14:11,208
What?! No way!

297
00:14:11,291 --> 00:14:13,041
Are you for real?

298
00:14:13,125 --> 00:14:14,041
I am.

299
00:14:14,125 --> 00:14:15,791
I can't believe
this is happening.

300
00:14:15,875 --> 00:14:17,791
Thank you so much!

301
00:14:17,875 --> 00:14:19,000
[CHIKA yelps]

302
00:14:19,083 --> 00:14:19,875
Hold up.

303
00:14:19,958 --> 00:14:21,583
I need to be clear about this.

304
00:14:21,666 --> 00:14:22,916
What?

305
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:24,416
I'm saying that I can help
you write a few songs

306
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:25,666
if you need me to.

307
00:14:25,750 --> 00:14:27,791
But I'm not signing up
to be a school idol.

308
00:14:27,875 --> 00:14:28,666
Aw...

309
00:14:28,750 --> 00:14:30,291
I don't have the time for it.

310
00:14:30,375 --> 00:14:31,416
Okay.

311
00:14:31,500 --> 00:14:33,291
We can't force her to, ya know.

312
00:14:33,375 --> 00:14:34,666
Yeah, don't remind me.

313
00:14:34,750 --> 00:14:36,666
Now just give me
the lines, please.

314
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:38,375
What lines?

315
00:14:39,083 --> 00:14:40,333
[CHIKA]
Lines?

316
00:14:40,416 --> 00:14:41,708
We have lines?

317
00:14:41,791 --> 00:14:43,375
Lines...

318
00:14:43,458 --> 00:14:44,750
Sorry, what lines?

319
00:14:44,833 --> 00:14:46,750
[YOU] ♪ She'll provide
the music for us to sing ♪

320
00:14:46,833 --> 00:14:48,791
♪ if we only give
her the lyrics! ♪

321
00:14:48,875 --> 00:14:50,625
--So, lyrics.
--Oh. Lyrics.

322
00:14:50,708 --> 00:14:51,916
This place?

323
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:53,666
I thought this was an inn!

324
00:14:53,750 --> 00:14:54,875
Yep, it is!

325
00:14:54,958 --> 00:14:56,583
[YOU]
This is a great place to relax!

326
00:14:56,666 --> 00:15:00,666
Plus, there's a bus stop nearby,
so getting home is a cinch!

327
00:15:00,750 --> 00:15:02,833
[SHIMA]
Welcome, girls! Come right in!

328
00:15:02,916 --> 00:15:04,708
You, you get cuter everyday!

329
00:15:04,791 --> 00:15:06,125
[YOU]
Aw! [laughs]

330
00:15:06,208 --> 00:15:08,041
So, Is this the girl you
were telling me about?

331
00:15:08,125 --> 00:15:09,875
[CHIKA]
Mm-hm! Say hello to Shima!

332
00:15:09,958 --> 00:15:13,625
[gasps] I'm Riko Sakurauchi.

333
00:15:13,708 --> 00:15:15,000
[SHIMA]
It's nice to meet you.

334
00:15:15,083 --> 00:15:16,375
She's so pretty!

335
00:15:16,458 --> 00:15:18,333
[CHIKA]
I think so, too! She looks like

336
00:15:18,416 --> 00:15:20,750
one of those Tokyo fashion
models, doesn't she?

337
00:15:20,833 --> 00:15:22,250
[SHIMA]
Absolutely.

338
00:15:22,333 --> 00:15:26,541
There's not much here today,
but make yourselves at home.

339
00:15:26,625 --> 00:15:28,000
[MITO]
Mm. Hey, Chika!

340
00:15:28,083 --> 00:15:29,666
[CHIKA]
What's up, Mito?

341
00:15:29,750 --> 00:15:31,375
Wait, is that my pudding?!

342
00:15:31,458 --> 00:15:32,125
It totally is!

343
00:15:32,208 --> 00:15:32,666
[SHIITAKE barks]

344
00:15:32,750 --> 00:15:34,333
[RIKO shrieks]

345
00:15:34,416 --> 00:15:36,625
[CHIKA]
Gimme back my pudding!

346
00:15:36,708 --> 00:15:39,000
[SHIITAKE howling]

347
00:15:39,083 --> 00:15:41,000
[CHIKA] How am I supposed
to focus on our work when

348
00:15:41,083 --> 00:15:44,083
the special pudding Shima bought
just for me was devoured.

349
00:15:44,166 --> 00:15:46,083
Is that even legal?

350
00:15:46,166 --> 00:15:48,625
Why don't we start
on the lyrics?

351
00:15:48,708 --> 00:15:51,583
We can't let food go to
waste! Ya snooze, ya lose!

352
00:15:51,666 --> 00:15:53,250
Oh, shut up!

353
00:15:53,333 --> 00:15:53,958
[gasps]

354
00:15:54,041 --> 00:15:55,958
Okay, you asked for it!

355
00:15:56,041 --> 00:15:56,750
Uh...

356
00:15:56,833 --> 00:15:58,708
Guess I missed...

357
00:15:58,791 --> 00:16:00,208
[ALL gasp]

358
00:16:01,208 --> 00:16:02,791
[RIKO]
Excuse us.

359
00:16:02,875 --> 00:16:04,583
Now, let's get started.

360
00:16:04,666 --> 00:16:07,416
Oh my gosh, I can't believe
you got a smartphone, finally!

361
00:16:07,500 --> 00:16:09,000
I know. I just got it!

362
00:16:09,083 --> 00:16:10,208
So cool!

363
00:16:10,291 --> 00:16:11,500
[CHIKA, YOU grunt]

364
00:16:11,583 --> 00:16:12,583
[MITO]
Run, Shiitake!

365
00:16:12,666 --> 00:16:15,083
[SHIITAKE barks]

366
00:16:15,166 --> 00:16:19,166
[RIKO] We're going to start
working on lyrics right now.

367
00:16:19,250 --> 00:16:20,041
[BOTH whimper]

368
00:16:20,125 --> 00:16:21,875
Kay!

369
00:16:26,166 --> 00:16:28,791
Maybe a love song is too
complicated to start with.

370
00:16:28,875 --> 00:16:32,083
No, we just need something great
like Mu's "Snow halation".

371
00:16:32,166 --> 00:16:33,291
It's hard to write about love

372
00:16:33,375 --> 00:16:34,916
when you have no
experience with it.

373
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:37,208
I've totally been
in love before!

374
00:16:37,291 --> 00:16:38,208
You have?

375
00:16:38,291 --> 00:16:39,458
[CHIKA grumbles]
Well, not really.

376
00:16:39,541 --> 00:16:42,333
I figured. We need
to write what we know.

377
00:16:42,416 --> 00:16:44,291
You know what? I wonder
if that means that one

378
00:16:44,375 --> 00:16:46,958
of the members of Mu's was in
love when they wrote that song.

379
00:16:47,041 --> 00:16:49,166
I would've never
thought about it!

380
00:16:49,250 --> 00:16:50,791
I have to look it up.

381
00:16:50,875 --> 00:16:52,958
[RIKO] Isn't there another time
you could be doing that?

382
00:16:53,041 --> 00:16:54,083
We're working here.

383
00:16:54,166 --> 00:16:55,583
I'm sorry, but I have to know.

384
00:16:55,666 --> 00:16:57,083
[RIKO]
Uh...

385
00:16:57,166 --> 00:16:58,500
Oh, Chika.

386
00:16:58,583 --> 00:17:00,958
She's absolutely in love
with school idols, isn't she?

387
00:17:01,041 --> 00:17:03,291
Seems like it. [gasps]

388
00:17:03,375 --> 00:17:04,666
[gasps]

389
00:17:07,125 --> 00:17:08,208
What is it?

390
00:17:08,291 --> 00:17:10,541
You have experience
with love after all.

391
00:17:10,625 --> 00:17:11,875
Why don't you try
writing lyrics

392
00:17:11,958 --> 00:17:13,833
using your special feelings
for school idols?

393
00:17:13,916 --> 00:17:16,125
Your first passion isn't
for another person...

394
00:17:16,208 --> 00:17:17,583
[RIKO]
...it's for Mu's!

395
00:17:17,666 --> 00:17:22,375
[CHIKA gasps]
Yeah, you're so right!

396
00:17:22,458 --> 00:17:25,291
I could write a million songs
about my love for them!

397
00:17:25,375 --> 00:17:27,541
Okay! First, I'm gonna
write all about how

398
00:17:27,625 --> 00:17:29,875
bright they shine
as a group!

399
00:17:34,041 --> 00:17:36,583
[PIANO TEACHER] Riko,
you're such a good pianist!

400
00:17:36,666 --> 00:17:38,500
[RIKO] Thank you!
I feel like I'm flying

401
00:17:38,583 --> 00:17:41,250
through the air when my
hands are on the keys.

402
00:17:41,333 --> 00:17:42,833
And I feel sparkly.

403
00:17:42,916 --> 00:17:44,166
Like the stars!

404
00:17:44,250 --> 00:17:46,333
I love it so much!

405
00:17:47,708 --> 00:17:48,625
[CHIKA]
Here!

406
00:17:48,708 --> 00:17:50,458
[RIKO gasps]
You're done already?

407
00:17:50,541 --> 00:17:53,666
It's not mine, but... this song
touched my heart so much

408
00:17:53,750 --> 00:17:55,458
I had to write it down.

409
00:17:55,541 --> 00:17:57,083
[RIKO]
"Yume no Tobira."

410
00:17:57,166 --> 00:17:59,583
[CHIKA] Yep! The second
I heard it, I was hooked!

411
00:17:59,666 --> 00:18:01,208
Then and there I decided,

412
00:18:01,291 --> 00:18:04,375
I had to help other people
feel the same joy I felt!

413
00:18:04,458 --> 00:18:05,791
You really want to give joy?

414
00:18:05,875 --> 00:18:07,333
Yep!

415
00:18:07,416 --> 00:18:09,166
I hadn't ever been inspired to
work toward anything before.

416
00:18:09,250 --> 00:18:11,250
But even I can make miracles!

417
00:18:11,333 --> 00:18:13,916
I'm learning to work hard
and put in the effort.

418
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:16,916
It sounds crazy, but
this'll bring out my best.

419
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:18,875
So I can shine!

420
00:18:18,958 --> 00:18:20,583
Mu's has done a lot for you.

421
00:18:20,666 --> 00:18:25,000
[CHIKA]
Uh. Mm-hm! I really love them!

422
00:18:45,708 --> 00:18:47,833
[CHIKA] They were just
average high schoolers.

423
00:18:47,916 --> 00:18:50,208
But when they all worked
together on that stage,

424
00:18:50,291 --> 00:18:52,250
they shined like the sun!

425
00:18:52,333 --> 00:18:54,708
I realized school idols were...

426
00:18:54,791 --> 00:18:59,041
Well, they were... they
were so incredibly radiant!

427
00:19:19,833 --> 00:19:22,958
[RIKO whimpering]

428
00:19:25,333 --> 00:19:28,500
[AUDIENCE murmuring]

429
00:19:39,500 --> 00:19:43,291
[piano plays]

430
00:19:43,375 --> 00:19:48,333
[singing in Japanese]

431
00:19:55,583 --> 00:20:00,583
[singing continues]

432
00:20:05,500 --> 00:20:08,291
[CHIKA gasping]

433
00:20:08,375 --> 00:20:09,083
[RIKO]
Chika?

434
00:20:09,166 --> 00:20:10,916
Well, hey there, neighbor!

435
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:13,833
I can't believe you
live right next door!

436
00:20:13,916 --> 00:20:15,000
[RIKO]
Yeah, me neither.

437
00:20:15,083 --> 00:20:17,583
We only just moved in,
so I had no idea!

438
00:20:17,666 --> 00:20:19,583
Were you playing the
song, "Yume no Tobira"?

439
00:20:19,666 --> 00:20:20,791
[RIKO]
Huh?

440
00:20:20,875 --> 00:20:21,833
I could hear you singing
through the window.

441
00:20:21,916 --> 00:20:24,583
No! Well, maybe.

442
00:20:24,666 --> 00:20:26,000
[CHIKA]
Don't you love the words?

443
00:20:26,083 --> 00:20:29,625
"I've been looking for
the door of dreams."

444
00:20:29,708 --> 00:20:31,041
[RIKO]
Yes. They're nice.

445
00:20:31,125 --> 00:20:33,708
It means so much to me I
could listen to it all night!

446
00:20:33,791 --> 00:20:34,666
It's from the second Love Live--

447
00:20:34,750 --> 00:20:35,500
[RIKO]
Listen...

448
00:20:35,583 --> 00:20:37,041
[CHIKA]
Uh. Huh?

449
00:20:37,125 --> 00:20:38,333
[RIKO]
I'm bored.

450
00:20:38,416 --> 00:20:41,041
Nothing is fun anymore.

451
00:20:41,125 --> 00:20:43,625
'Cause my passions
aren't making me happy.

452
00:20:43,708 --> 00:20:45,083
And I've been trying so hard.

453
00:20:45,166 --> 00:20:48,375
One more time.

454
00:20:48,458 --> 00:20:51,750
Would you wanna...
become a school idol?

455
00:20:51,833 --> 00:20:53,250
I can't.

456
00:20:53,333 --> 00:20:56,041
There's no way I that I could
give up playing the piano.

457
00:20:56,125 --> 00:20:57,250
You don't have to!

458
00:20:57,333 --> 00:20:58,791
But try something fresh.

459
00:20:58,875 --> 00:21:01,500
It could inspire you
in a whole new way.

460
00:21:01,583 --> 00:21:04,041
Then you can go back
to what you love!

461
00:21:04,125 --> 00:21:05,791
It's not fair.

462
00:21:05,875 --> 00:21:08,666
Becoming a school
idol is your dream.

463
00:21:08,750 --> 00:21:14,291
And I'd be using it just
for motivation, you know?

464
00:21:14,375 --> 00:21:16,541
[CHIKA] If it helps you at all,
it'll be worth it.

465
00:21:16,625 --> 00:21:18,083
That's why I'm doing this.

466
00:21:18,166 --> 00:21:20,916
Listen. Find your joy!

467
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:23,583
That's what being a
school idol is all about!

468
00:21:23,666 --> 00:21:25,166
[gasping]

469
00:21:25,250 --> 00:21:27,250
Uh! Chika!

470
00:21:30,416 --> 00:21:31,875
I have faith!

471
00:21:31,958 --> 00:21:35,291
I know in my heart this
is the right thing to do!

472
00:21:38,958 --> 00:21:41,958
[BOTH grunting]

473
00:21:42,041 --> 00:21:44,000
Uh. That's far enough.

474
00:21:44,083 --> 00:21:45,250
We aren't able to reach, so--

475
00:21:45,333 --> 00:21:48,000
Riko! Don't quit!

476
00:21:52,083 --> 00:21:53,166
[RIKO]
Uh.

477
00:21:54,833 --> 00:21:58,791
[BOTH grunting]

478
00:22:08,750 --> 00:22:11,416
[RIKO laughs]

479
00:22:12,375 --> 00:22:15,125
[CHIKA laughs]

480
00:23:46,875 --> 00:23:50,833
[CHIKA, YOU, RIKO]
Next time, "First step!"

